SETTING UP A TESTING ENVIRONMENT

1. pip install pytest
2. pip install pytest-django
3. pip install pytest-factoryboy -> it helps us to generate data automatically and dynamically
4. pip install pytest-selenium

To ensure quality throughout the whole software engineering lifecycle here

Creating a testing ENVIRONMENT
1. create an app called dashboard inside the ecommerce app
2. create a folder in the dashboard app and name it tests
3. inside the tests folder, to make it discoverable create a file called init.py 
4. inside the tests folder create another file called test_selenium_dashboard.py to test the selinium 

CREATING A CONFIGURATION file
1. create a pytest.ini file at where the manage.py file is located
2. Do your customisation in that file called pytest.ini file
